Adjust racks to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced).

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and lightly browned, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and 1⁄4 tsp @italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}; lightly season with salt and pepper (you'll use the rest of the Italian Seasoning later).

Cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small serving bowl{}. Stir in half the lemon zest. Wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain and transfer to a large #serving bowl{}; toss with a drizzle of @olive oil{}(large drizzle for 4 servings). Reserve pot.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add @italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add onion and lightly season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

While sausage cooks, in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @marinara sauce{14%ounce}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining Italian Seasoning, and @water{1/4%cup}(for 4 servings: 1/3 cup).

Cover tightly with @plastic wrap{} and microwave until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

In a second #medium bowl{}, combine @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce}, remaining garlic powder, and @water{3/4%cup}(for 4 servings: 1 1/2 cups).

Heat pot used for cavatappi over medium-high heat. Add cheese roux mixture and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and whisk in @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, remaining lemon zest, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Cook, stirring, until cream cheese has melted, ~{1%minute}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Transfer to a small serving bowl; cover tightly with plastic wrap to keep warm.

Carefully uncover red sauce and cream sauce (watch out for steam!).

> If needed, microwave sauces in 30-second increments until warmed through.

Serve pasta, red sauce, cream sauce, zucchini, sausage and onion, panko, @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and remaining lemon wedges family style and let everyone build their own pasta bowl.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.